{{Object | Name=Jaguar XK8 | Guid=3055-7494 | Deck=The 1997 Jaguar XK8 (X100) is a grand tourer convertible and coupe of the Jaguar XK (X100) generation. Production was launched in 1999 and ceased in 2006. The name XK8 is a reference to the engine of the car. | Characters= | Concepts=Concepts/Jaguar_Cars_Ltd,Concepts/Licensed_Cars | Franchises= | Games=Games/Europe_Racer,Games/Gran_Turismo_2,Games/Headhunter,Games/London_Racer,Games/Need_for_Speed_III_Hot_Pursuit,Games/Top_Drives | Locations=Locations/United_Kingdom | People= | Objects=Objects/Car,Objects/Jaguar_XK,Objects/Jaguar_XKR_X100,Objects/Sports_Car | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/151/1511438/3645505-4812016327-1000.jpg }}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"3645505-4812016327-1000.jpg","path":"151\/1511438\/","mime":"image\/jpeg","sizes":"square_tiny,square_medium,square_small,square_avatar,scale_super,square_mini,scale_medium,scale_small,scale_avatar,scale_large,screen_medium,screen_kubrick","caption":null},"background":[]}' /> The XK8 was the entry level model of the XK series, whilst the XKR was the top-range model. Both the [[Objects/Aston_Martin_DB7|Aston Martin DB7]] and the XK8 are based on the Jaguar XJS.
===''NEED FOR SPEED III: HOT PURSUIT''=== The XK8 appears in the PC release of ''Need for Speed III: Hot Pursuit'' as a class C vehicle. Compared to the Aston Martin DB7 and [[Objects/Mercedes_Benz_SL600|Mercedes-Benz SL 600]], the XK8 has worse acceleration and top speed. The lack of power is compensated by a controllable and precise steering. The model featured in the game is the convertible version despite official images of the vehicle featured in the showcase and loading slide being from the coupe model.

{{Object | Name=Land-Rover Range Rover | Guid=3055-7567 | Deck=The Land Rover Range Rover, generally shortened to Range Rover, is a 4x4 luxury SUV produced by Land Rover, a marque and sub-brand of Jaguar Land Rover. The Range Rover line was launched in 1970 by British Leyland and is now in its fifth generation. | Characters= | Concepts=Concepts/Licensed_Cars | Franchises= | Games=Games/Enthusia_Professional_Racing,Games/Forza_Horizon,Games/Forza_Horizon_2,Games/Forza_Horizon_3,Games/Forza_Horizon_4,Games/Forza_Horizon_5,Games/Forza_Motorsport_3,Games/Forza_Motorsport_4,Games/Forza_Motorsport_5,Games/Forza_Motorsport_6,Games/Forza_Motorsport_6_Apex,Games/Forza_Motorsport_7,Games/NBA_Ballers,Games/The_Getaway,Games/Top_Drives | Locations=Locations/United_Kingdom | People= | Objects=Objects/Car,Objects/Sports_Utility_Vehicle | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/151/1511438/3645791-3449165364-latest.png }}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"3645791-3449165364-latest.png","path":"151\/1511438\/","mime":"image\/png","sizes":"square_medium,square_avatar,square_small,scale_super,square_tiny,scale_small,scale_medium,square_mini,scale_avatar,scale_large,screen_medium,screen_kubrick","caption":null},"background":[]}' />
===History=== * &lt;p&gt;The 1973 Range Rover - also known as "Range Rover Classic" - is the third model year of the original Range Rover that was only available as a two-door model until 1981. It appears in Forza Horizon 4 and 5.&lt;/p&gt; * &lt;p&gt;The Land Rover Range Rover (L322) is the third-generation Range Rover model from British car maker Land Rover and was originally developed under the codename 'L30'. The 2012 version appears in ''Forza Horizon'', ''Forza Motorsport 5 ''and ''Forza Motorsport 7'' and the 2008 one appears in ''Forza Motorsport 3'' and ''Forza Motorsport 4''.&lt;/p&gt; * The fourth generation called L405 appears in ''Forza Horizon 2'' as part of the ''NAPA Auto Parts Car Pack'', ''Forza Motorsport 6'' and ''Forza Horizon 3''. &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

{{Object | Name=Life Transformer Gun | Guid=3055-7669 | Deck=A gun designed to return a mutant back to their original form. | Characters=Characters/Shredder | Concepts= | Franchises= | Games=Games/Teenage_Mutant_Ninja_Turtles,Games/Teenage_Mutant_Ninja_Turtles_The_Cowabunga_Collection | Locations=Locations/The_Technodrome | People= | Objects=Objects/Gun,Objects/Mutagen_Ooze | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/16/164924/3690678-5075227730-latest.png }}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"3690678-5075227730-latest.png","path":"16\/164924\/","mime":"image\/png","sizes":"scale_medium,scale_small,square_avatar,scale_super,square_small,square_medium,square_tiny,square_mini,scale_large,scale_avatar,screen_kubrick,screen_medium","caption":null},"background":[]}' />
==Overview== The '''Life Transformer Gun''' is a weapon utilized by [[Characters/Shredder|Shredder]] in his boss fight in ''[[Games/Teenage_Mutant_Ninja_Turtles|Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]].'' Its shots are capable of turning the Ninja Turtles back into ordinary pets. After his defeat, the Turtles use it to transform [[Characters/Splinter|Splinter]] back into [[Characters/Hamato_Yoshi|Hamato Yoshi]]. It is an adaptation of a similar device seen in the TV series, the Retro Mutagen Ray Generator.
